Class InstanceModificationException

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class InstanceModificationException
extends java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
    Author:
    Connor Vann

    This extends from the superclass IllegalArgumentException to throw an Exception when data is modified in an Instance. This will only be thrown if the value has already been set, similar to how an IDE would handle a final field.
